hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: We'll need to take up references zytenz dangers In a pretty village in the Forest of Dean on a sunny September morning I met Alison and Tim Bulbeck, the nicest pair of Neat and Tidy (NAT) gardeners you could wish to meet. They left the safe suburbs early this year and, whilst keen as mustard to make the most of their lovely plot, they are seriously under siege from invading rural weeds and, by their own admission, have no knowledge of shrub pruning beyond "hack it down and see what happens". They share the gardening along utterly traditional NAT lines: he does mowing and big stuff, she does flowers and fiddly bits.
